$interpreted: Yu: What is this? You intrude, cause trouble, yet won't state your name?
Tindoiimu: Hah! Trouble? Clearly it's your soldiers who are causing trouble.
Tindoiimu: An army this undisciplined, and its general completely unaware. Ought to cost you your job!
Yu: My soldiers? Trouble?
Yu: I'm afraid you're mistaken.
Yu: My soldiers' actions are completely justified.
Tindoiimu: You were aware of this!? You deliberately allow them to abuse our people!?
Yu: Do you know how difficult it is for soldiers stationed on the borders?
Yu: The battlefield makes one go mad! The Insect Tribe is infuriatingly uncooperative, and yet the Alliance does NOTHING but...
Yu: The point is, it is not easy to lead troops full of pent-up frustration. They need ways to release their stress, their anger.
Tindoiimu: Twisted, crooked reasoning!
Astonished Insect: P-Princess? Princess Tindoiimu!?
Astonished Insect: A butterfly... with such an imposing manner. It must be, it really is the princess!
Yu: Tindoiimu... the political hostage sent to the Qilin Tribe nine years ago?
Tindoiimu: ......
Yu: The royal family. No wonder you've got such an attitude.
Yu: Interesting. Arriving here so suddenly. Could you have escaped and fled home!?
Tindoiimu: ......
Yu: Not afraid? Bold.
Yu: Pests, if you want to protect your princess...
Yu: ...feel free to join in. I won't mind.
Scared Insect: I-I-If the royal family didn't surrender for fear of death, we wouldn't have all fallen into such a sad state...
Scared Insect 2: Yeah... the princess is living a life of comfort in the Alliance... she's basically forgotten all about us!
Scared Insect: The r-r-royal family won't protect us. Why would we protect her!?
Scared Insect 2: Plus, how could we beat a general from the Tiger Tribe...
Yu: *spits* Spineless cowards!
Tindoiimu: .........
Tindoiimu: ...I will not permit you to humiliate my people in front of me. Take that back!
Yu: You heard what they think of you. Why would you speak for them?
Tindoiimu: ...They're not wrong. The royal family ought to protect them. We have failed our people.
Yu: ...Noble. You may be a pest, but you are of the royal family. I wish that Alliance scum could hear you say that.
Yu: As this is the case, I will do my best to leave your four limbs intact.
Juan Yun: Wait a moment! General, please stop!
Yu: ...Qilin Tribe?
Juan Yun: *huff*...*puff*... Sir... I am Juan Yun of the Qilin Tribe.
Juan Yun: I invited the princess to come along, she has not escaped! Please understand, General!
Yu: I am only acquainted with the chieftain of the Qilin Tribe, and am unaware of you. You say she was invited here, but do you have proof?
Juan Yun: Um... We were separated from Arbiter Maeok and the diplomats...
Yu: So that means no.
Yu: You may be a descendant of mythics, but that doesn't mean I release fugitives on your word alone!
Juan Yun: The general is not well-versed in emotions. It does not matter how you treat me, but as for this beautiful woman...
Yu: ...Long ago, the mythics could split mountains and move oceans with their own power. There was not a tiger who did not cower before them.
Yu: To this very day, respect is paid to descendents of the three mythics.
Juan Yun: Thank you, general, you are too kind~
Yu: —Yet the power of mythics today pales in comparison to those of old. Shameless, using the name of one's ancestors to win favor.
Juan Yun: Eh? Wait a second, the general is mistaken. I would absolutely—
Tindoiimu: ...It's getting harder and harder to keep this guy out of trouble...
Yu: I only recognize real power, not some empty name!
Yu: If you're involved in harboring a fugitive, I'll take you down all the same!
Yu: As expected, you have some skills. I'll finish this right here. HARGHH!!!
Kong Maeok: Stop!
Yu: ...Arbiter Maeok?
Kong Maeok: General Yu, your soldier has already told me what happened.
Kong Maeok: Tindoiimu did receive my permission to follow us back to her homeland. She is not a fugitive on the run.
Yu: ...Still as careless as ever.
Yu: The soldiers of the Tiger Tribe are dying on the frontlines and you bring back an enemy hostage like it's nothing.
Kong Maeok: General Yu, don't speak like that. The Insect Tribe is now part of the Alliance.
Kong Maeok: We ought to aspire to treat everyone as family...
Yu: Do I dare ask how many tiger soldiers died so the Alliance can say that everyone is "family"?
Kong Maeok: Ah, I...
Yu: Speaking of the Alliance Army... for many years, each tribe has remained peacefully on their own land.
Yu: Yet it is clear that the Tiger Tribe is alone on the borders, fighting your war. Isn't that so?
Kong Maeok: That is not true! I proposed to send assistance, but...
Diplomatic Ambassador: Impudence! If we had not shown such great mercy, the heinous crimes of the tiger king would have sent the Tiger Tribe to—
Kong Maeok: O-Okay! Enough! We're just here to look around.
Kong Maeok: General Yu, since you are responsible for supervising the Insect Tribe, please lead the way.
Yu: The border paths are rugged and craggy. All of you watch your precious little steps.
